  "prompt": "What do people in Miami wear in the winter?",
  "response": "Miami winters are famously mild, so the fashion is all about layering and adapting to temperatures that can range from comfortably warm to slightly chilly. Here's a breakdown of what people wear:\n\n**General Trends:**\n\n*   **Light Layers are Key:** Think lightweight fabrics like linen, cotton, and rayon. Layers allow you to adjust as the temperature fluctuates throughout the day.\n*   **Comfortable Shoes:** Sandals, sneakers, and espadrilles are all common. You'll be doing a lot of walking, so comfort is important.\n*   **Sun Protection Still Matters:** The sun is still strong, so sunglasses, hats, and sunscreen are essential.\n*   **\"Miami Chic\" Style:** Even in winter, Miami style tends to be vibrant, stylish, and slightly more dressed-up than in other casual climates.\n*   **It can be cool at night:** Some nights can get chilly, especially closer to the coast, so people will dress warmly for night outings.\n\n**Specific Clothing Items:**\n\n*   **Tops:**\n    *   T-shirts (short and long-sleeved)\n    *   Tank tops\n    *   Lightweight button-down shirts (linen or cotton)\n    *   Sweaters: Lightweight cardigans, thin knit sweaters, and fashionable hoodies.\n    *   Blouses\n*   **Bottoms:**\n    *   Jeans (especially lighter washes or white denim)\n    *   Shorts (still wearable on warmer days)\n    *   Skirts (mini, midi, and maxi)\n    *   Lightweight pants (linen, chinos, dress pants)\n    *   Leggings\n*   **Dresses:**\n    *   Sundresses\n    *   Maxi dresses\n    *   Cocktail dresses (for evenings out)\n*   **Outerwear:**\n    *   Light jackets (denim, leather, bomber)\n    *   Cardigans\n    *   Wraps or shawls\n    *   Light trench coats (rarely needed, but can be stylish)\n*   **Shoes:**\n    *   Sandals (especially during the day)\n    *   Sneakers\n    *   Espadrilles\n    *   Flats\n    *   Ankle boots (for a more fashionable look, especially in the evenings)\n    *   Heels (for evenings and special occasions)\n*   **Accessories:**\n    *   Sunglasses\n    *   Hats (baseball caps, fedoras, wide-brimmed hats)\n    *   Scarves (lightweight silk or cotton)\n    *   Jewelry (gold and silver are both popular)\n    *   Beach bags or totes\n\n**Key Differences from Summer:**\n\n*   **Fewer bright neon colors:** While Miami is colorful year-round, winter may see slightly more muted tones or darker colors interspersed with the brights.\n*   **More closed-toe shoes:** Sandals are still worn, but you'll see more sneakers, flats, and ankle boots.\n*   **More layers:** The biggest difference is the addition of lightweight layers for warmth.\n*   **Less swimwear:** While you might still see some people in swimwear at the beach or pool, it's less prevalent than in the summer.\n\n**In summary, think \"stylish, comfortable, and adaptable\" when packing or choosing your winter wardrobe in Miami. You'll want pieces that can be easily layered and that reflect the city's vibrant and relaxed vibe.**\n",
